    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>steak </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature</p><p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat, once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/teriyaki-rump-steak-with-brown-rice-and-sesame-pak-choi/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice your <strong>pak choi</strong> in half, lengthways</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/teriyaki-rump-steak-with-brown-rice-and-sesame-pak-choi/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan over a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and once very hot, add your<strong> steak[s]</strong></p><p>For rare, cook for 2-3 min max on each side; for medium-rare, cook for 3-4 min on each side; for medium, cook for 4-5 min on each side</p><p>Tip: don't be tempted to move the steaks around too much in the pan \u2013 this will stop them from browning</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/teriyaki-rump-steak-with-brown-rice-and-sesame-pak-choi/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a separate pan with a matching lid over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame oil</strong> and <strong>pak choi</strong>, cut-side down, and cook for 2-3 min or until slightly brown</p><p>Once brown, add a splash of <strong>warm water</strong> and cook, covered, for 4-5 min further or until soft</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/teriyaki-rump-steak-with-brown-rice-and-sesame-pak-choi/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once done, transfer the<strong> cooked steaks</strong> to a shallow plate and leave them to rest</p><p>Reserve the steak pan for later</p><p>Combine your <strong>cornflour</strong>, <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, <strong>soy sauce </strong>and <strong>honey </strong>with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>teriyaki sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/teriyaki-rump-steak-with-brown-rice-and-sesame-pak-choi/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove the steak pan from the heat, add the <strong>teriyaki sauce</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Tip: this will cool the pan down and prevent the honey from burning!</p><p>Return the pan to a medium-low heat and cook for 3-4 min or until a thick and sticky sauce remains \u2013 this is your <strong>teriyaki sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/teriyaki-rump-steak-with-brown-rice-and-sesame-pak-choi/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>rested steaks</strong> finely</p><p>Stir any of the <strong>resting juices</strong> through the <strong>teriyaki sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/teriyaki-rump-steak-with-brown-rice-and-sesame-pak-choi/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sliced steak</strong> with the <strong>rice</strong> and<strong> sesame pak choi</strong> to the side</p><p>Tip: for fancy presentation, press the rice into a small bowl and turn out</p><p>Pour the <strong>teriyaki sauce</strong> over the steak and garnish with your <strong>crispy onions</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
